payloads.name: Hot Bird 6
payloads.description: The Hot Bird 6 satellite will provide 32 active transponders, 28 of these will operate in the Ku-band, he remaining 4 will operate in the Ka-band. payloads.name: Hellas-Sat 2
payloads.description: The high-power Hellas-Sat 2 spacecraft is a Eurostar-2000+ model equipped with 30 active FSS transponders operating in Ku-band, allowing the transmission of digital TV direct to home receive antennas as small as 60 cm.

payloads.name: MRO
payloads.description: The Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter (MRO) will make high-resolution measurements of the surface from orbit. payloads.name: FalconSat 2

payloads.name: Astra 1KR

payloads.name: ASTRO
payloads.description: The Orbital Express advanced technology demonstrator has the capability to autonomously service and refuel satellites while onorbit. The Boeing team built the Autonomous Space Transport Robotic Operations satellite, and the NEXTSat/CSC, and conducted an on orbit demonstration.

payloads.name: NEXTSat

payloads.name: STPSat 1

payloads.name: CFESat

payloads.name: MidSTAR 1
payloads.description: MidSTAR-1 is the first implementation of the MidSTAR-1 mod 1 bus design. payloads.name: FalconSat 3

payloads.name: OSIRIS-REx
payloads.description: NASA has selected the University of Arizona to lead the OSIRIS-REx (Origins, Spectral Interpretation, Resource Identification, Security –Regolith Explorer) sample-return mission to an asteroid.

payloads.name: WorldView 4
payloads.description: WorldView 4, formerly known as GeoEye 2, is a commercial high-rsolution earth observation satellite operated by DigitalGlobe. WorldView-4 provides 31 cm panchromatic resolution, and 1.24 m multispectral resolution.

payloads.name: RAVAN
payloads.description: RAVAN (Radiometer Assessment using Vertically Aligned Nanotubes) is low-cost cubesat mission led by the Johns Hopkins Applied Physics Laboratory in Laurel, Md., to demonstrate technology needed to measure the absolute imbalance in the Earth's radiation budget (ERI).

payloads.name: OptiCube 4
payloads.description: The OptiCube 4 (O/C 4 or Optical Cube) satellite, developed by Cal Poly, is a 2U CubeSats to provide on-orbit targets for ground assets to calibrate sensors for orbital debris studies and small-object tracking improvements.

payloads.name: AeroCube 8C
payloads.description: Aerocube 8 (AC8) or IMPACT (), is a two satellite cubesat mission by the Aerospace Corporation of El Segundo to demonstrate a new electric propulsion, nanotechnologies (CNT) and solar cell technologies.

payloads.name: AeroCube 8D
payloads.description: Aerocube 8 (AC8) or IMPACT (), is a two satellite cubesat mission by the Aerospace Corporation of El Segundo to demonstrate a new electric propulsion, nanotechnologies (CNT) and solar cell technologies.

payloads.name: Prometheus-2.1
payloads.description: Prometheus is series of 1.5U CubeSats for technology development and demonstration. Developed by the Los Alamos National Laboratory with the objectives of evaluating low-cost development and operations methodologies while also assessing the operational utility that can be provided by a CubeSat.

payloads.name: Prometheus-2.3
payloads.description: Prometheus is series of 1.5U CubeSats for technology development and demonstration. payloads.name: CELTEE 1
payloads.description: CELTEE 1 (CubeSat Enhanced Locator Transponder Evaluation Experiment 1) is picosatellite built by M42 Technologies (Seattle,WA) for the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL). It is built to the 1U CubeSat form factor.

payloads.name: SBIRS-GEO 3
payloads.description: SBIRS-GEO (Space Based Infra Red Sensor - Geostationary) is the geostationary component of the SBIRS-High program, which will replace the DSP system of early warning satellites in providing early warning for Intercontinental Ballistic Missile launches.

payloads.name: SAGE 3
payloads.description: The SAGE 3 (Stratospheric Aerosol and Gas Experiment) is the third generation of solar occultation instruments operated by NASA, with additional elements added to accommodate installation and operation on the International Space Station (ISS).

payloads.name: STP-H5
payloads.description: The STP-H5 (Space Test Program - Houston 5) is a combo of experiments to be hosted on the International Space Station (ISS).

payloads.name: Intruder 12A
payloads.description: NOSS-3 (Naval Ocean Surveillance System), which is likely not the official designation, is the third generation of NOSS satellites, which are low orbit SIGINT satellites. In 2013, the designation Intruder leaked out.

payloads.name: Intruder 12B
payloads.description: NOSS-3 (Naval Ocean Surveillance System), which is likely not the official designation, is the third generation of NOSS satellites, which are low orbit SIGINT satellites. In 2013, the designation Intruder leaked out.

payloads.name: Cygnus CRS-7
payloads.description: Orbital and NASA's Johnson Space Center are jointly developing a new space transportation system in a three-year cooperative program to support the International Space Station (ISS).

payloads.name: Altair 1
payloads.description:
Altair Pathfinder [Millenium Space]

ALTAIR Pathfinder or ALTAIR 1 is a 1×6U CubeSat technology demonstration mission by Millennium Space Systems.

payloads.name: SUSat
payloads.description: SUSat (University of Adelaide Satellite) is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at the University of Adelaide.

payloads.name: UNSW-EC0
payloads.description: UNSW-EC0 is an Australian 2U-CubeSat designed by Australian Centre for Space Engineering Research at the University of New South Wales participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: i-INSPIRE 2
payloads.description: i-INSPIRE 2 is an Australian 2U-CubeSat designed by University of Sydney participating in the QB50 project, which demonstrates the possibility of launching a network of 50 CubeSats built by Teams all over the world to perform first-class science in the largely unexplored lower thermosphere.

payloads.name: ZA-AeroSat
payloads.description: ZA-AeroSat is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at the Stellenbosch University, South Africa.

payloads.name: nSIGHT 1
payloads.description: nSIGHT 1 is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at SCS-Space, South Africa.

payloads.name: Ex-Alta 1
payloads.description: Ex-Alta 1 (Experimental Albertan 1) is a Canadian 3U-CubeSat designed by the Department of Physics of the University of Alberta participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: LilacSat 1
payloads.description: LilacSat 1 is a 2U-CubeSat for education, upper atmosphere science, amateur radio communication and technology demonstration, built by a team of students of Harbin Institute of Technology (HIT).

payloads.name: NJUST 1
payloads.description: NJUST 1 is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at Nanjin University of Science and Technology (NJUST).

payloads.name: Aoxiang 1
payloads.description: AoXiang 1 is a 2U-CubeSat designed and built at the Shaanxi Engineering Laboratory (SELM), Northwestern Polytechnical University (NPU).

payloads.name: SOMP 2
payloads.description: SOMP 2 (Student's Oxygen Measurement Project 2) is a student picosat project of the Techniche Universität Dresden. It is built to the 2U-CubeSat) form factor.

payloads.name: QBITO
payloads.description: QBITO is a Spanish 2U-CubeSat designed by E-USOC (Spanish User Support and Operations Centre) at the Polytechnic University of Madrid participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: Aalto 2
payloads.description: Aalto 2 is a 2U-CubeSat mission built by the Aalto University of Aalto, Finland.

payloads.name: X-CubeSat
payloads.description: X-CubeSat 1 is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at École polytechnique.

payloads.name: SpaceCube
payloads.description: SpaceCube is a 2U-CubeSat for technolgy development and upper atmosphere science. It is developed and built at Mines ParisTech.

payloads.name: DUTHSat
payloads.description: DUTHSat (Democritus University of Thrace Satellite) is a Greek 2U-CubeSat constructed by the Democritus University of Thrace (DUTH) Space Research Laboratory part of the QB50 mission.

payloads.name: UPSat
payloads.description: UPSat (University of Patras Satellite) is a Greek 2U-CubeSat constructed by University of Patras and Libre Space Foundation part of the QB50 mission with ID GR-02.

payloads.name: Hoopoe
payloads.description: Hoopoe is an Israeli 2U-CubeSat constructed by the Space Laboratory of the Herzliya Science Center as part of the QB50 mission.

payloads.name: LINK
payloads.description: LINK (Little Intelligent Nanosatellite of KAIST), is a South Korean 2U-CubeSat designed by KAIST participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: SNUSAT 1
payloads.description: SNUSAT 1 (Seoul National University Satellite 1), is a South Korean 2U-CubeSat designed by the Seoul National University participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: SNUSAT 1b
payloads.description: SNUSAT 1 (Seoul National University Satellite 1), is a South Korean 2U-CubeSat designed by the Seoul National University participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: qbee50-LTU-OC
payloads.description: qbee50-LTU-OC is a Swedish 2U-CubeSat designed and produced by Open Cosmos Ltd for QB50 in collaboration with Luleå Tekniska Universitet (LTU) that provides integration, test and ground station facilities and support. The mission participates in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: BeEagleSat
payloads.description: BeEagleSat is a 2U CubeSat to be launched within the EU FP7 project QB 50. It is being produced by Istanbul Technical University and Turkish Air Force Academy. Sabanci University provided a CdZnTe based semiconductor X-ray detector and associated readout electronics.

payloads.name: HAVELSAT
payloads.description: HAVELSAT is a 2U CubeSat to be launched within the EU FP7 project QB 50. It is built jointly by HAVELSAN and Istanbul Technical University.

payloads.name: Phoenix
payloads.description: Phoenix is a 2U-CubeSat for upper atmosphere science and technology demonstration, built by a team of students of National Cheng Kung University (NCKU).

payloads.name: PolyITAN 2-SAU
payloads.description: PolyITAN-2-SAU is a 2U CubeSat designed and built by the National Technical University of Ukraine – KPI in cooperation with the Ukrainian HAM radio community. The mission participates in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: QBUS 1
payloads.description:
QBUS 1 [University of Colorado]

QBUS 1 or Challenger is an US 2U-CubeSat designed by the University of Colorado Boulder participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: QBUS 2
payloads.description: QBUS 2 or Atlantis is an US 2U-CubeSat designed by the University of Michigan participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: QBUS 4
payloads.description: QBUS 4 or Columbia is an US 2U-CubeSat designed by the Universidad del Turabo, Puerto Rico, participating in the QB50 project.

payloads.name: IceCube
payloads.description: IceCube or Earth 1 is a 3U CubeSat mission developed by NASA's Goddard Space Flight Center to evaluate sub-mm-wave remote sensing from a CubeSat.

payloads.name: CSUNSat 1
payloads.description: The CSUNSat 1 (California State University Northridge Satellite 1) is an 2U CubeSat mission developed at the California State University Northridge (CSUN) in partnership with the Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL) to space validate a new low temperature energy storage system developed at JPL.

payloads.name: CXBN 2
payloads.description: CXBN (Cosmic X-Ray Background) is a nanosatellite designed to make observations of the diffuse X-ray background and publish the data. It is build on a double CubeSat form factor.

payloads.name: KySat 3
payloads.description: KySat-2 is a cube shaped picosat-class CubeSat satellite powered by solar energy, weighs 1 kg and measures 10 cm on a side.

payloads.name: SHARC
payloads.description: SHARC (Satellite for High Accuracy Radar Calibration) is picosatellite built by the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) to provide radar calibration for ground based radars. It is built to the non-standard 5U (1×5U) CubeSat form factor.

payloads.name: TDRA 13 M
payloads.description: NASA selected Boeing in December 2007 to built the third generation of TDRS (Tracking & Data Relay Satellite) data relay satellites. They are the successors of the second generation TDRS satellites.

payloads.name: SBIRS-GEO 4
payloads.description: SBIRS-GEO (Space Based Infra Red Sensor - Geostationary) is the geostationary component of the SBIRS-High program, which will replace the DSP system of early warning satellites in providing early warning for Intercontinental Ballistic Missile launches.

payloads.name: InSight
payloads.description: NASA selected in August 2012 the 12th mission of the Discovery program. The new mission, named InSight (Interior Exploration using Seismic Investigations, Geodesy and Heat Transport, will place instruments on the Martian surface to investigate whether the core of Mars is solid or liquid like Earth.

payloads.name: MarCO A
payloads.description: MarCO (Mars Cube One) is a two spacecraft mission to accompany the InSight Mars lander to provide real-time data relay during the landing phase, as the MRO, MAVEN, and Mars Odyssey orbiters will not be in position to receive InSight data. The probes are nick-named Wall-E and Eva.

payloads.name: MarCO B
payloads.description: MarCO (Mars Cube One) is a two spacecraft mission to accompany the InSight Mars lander to provide real-time data relay during the landing phase, as the MRO, MAVEN, and Mars Odyssey orbiters will not be in position to receive InSight data. The probes are nick-named Wall-E and Eva.

payloads.name: Bangabandu 1
payloads.description: Bangabandhu 1 is the first Bangladeshian geostationary communications satellite. The satellite was ordered in November 2015 from Thales Alenia Space, who will build, launch and operate the satellite for the Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission.

payloads.name: GRACE-FO 1
payloads.description: GRACE-FO (Gravity Recovery And Climate Experiment - Follow On) mission is the successor to the GRACE mission. For a minimum of five years from August 2017, the GRACE-FO mission will continue the extremely accurate measurement data collection of the first twin GRACE satellites.

payloads.name: GRACE-FO 2
payloads.description: GRACE-FO (Gravity Recovery And Climate Experiment - Follow On) mission is the successor to the GRACE mission. payloads.name: SEC 12
payloads.description: SES 12 is a powerful geostationary communications satellite operating in Ku- and Ka-bands, which uses electric propulsion for initial orbit raising and all on-orbit manoeuvres.

payloads.name: Dragon CRS-15
payloads.description: Dragon is a space capsule designed by SpaceX to provide supplies to the International space station.

payloads.name: ECOSTRESS
payloads.description: The ECOSTRESS (Ecosystem Spaceborne Thermal Radiometer Experiment on Space Station) will measure the temperature of plants and use that information to better understand how much water plants need and how they respond to stress.

payloads.name: Biarri-Squad 1
payloads.description: The Biarri project is a four nation defence related project involving Australia, the US, the UK and Canada to build three 3U CubeSats for precision flying experiments and a risk mitigation satellite.
